<h2>DIETARY RECCOMENDATION</h2>

<main>
<p>NUTRITION FOR THE MENSTRUAL PHASE</p>
<br>
<br>
  <p1>what is happening?
<br>
   At this stage,estrogen and progesterone levels are low. The lining of the uterus, called the endometrium, is shed, causing bleeding. 
<br> 
<br>
   FOOD FOCUS:Add nutrients; warmth and comfort
<br>
<br>
   MUST INCLUDE:</p1>
   <ul>
  <li>Sea vegetables e.g. kelp</li>
  <li> Sweet potato</li>
  <li> Activated brown rice</li>
    <li>  Kefir or probiotic yoghurts</li>
    <li>Pumpkin seeds</li>
    <li>Millet- based cereals</li>
    <li>Wheat germ</li>
    <li>Protein of choice; beef, chicken, lentils, fish, eggs, tofu</li>
    <li>Nuts</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>NUTRITION FOR THE FOLLICULAR PHASE</p>
    <br>
    <br>
      <p1>what is happening?
    <br>
       At this stage,Estrogen and progesterone are on the rise.
    </p2>
    <br> 
    <br>
       FOOD FOCUS:Fresh and light
    <br>
    <br>
       MUST INCLUDE:</p1>
       <ul>
      <li>Salad vegetables</li>
      <li>Flaxseeds </li>
      <li> Avocado</li>
        <li> Broccoli</li>
        <li>Nuts/seed mix </li>
        <li>Probiotic yoghurt</li>
        <li>Zucchini/ courgettes</li>
        <li>Buckwheat</li>
        <li>Salmon</li>
        <li>Kefir</li>
        </ul>

        <p>NUTRITION FOR THE OVULATORY PHASE</p>
        <br>
        <br>
          <p1>what is happening?
        <br>
           At this stage,estrogen peaks.Testosterone and progesterone levels are on the rise.
        <br> 
        <br>
           FOOD FOCUS:Fibrous and light
        <br>
        <br>
           MUST INCLUDE:</p1>
           <ul>
          <li>Quinoa</li>
          <li>Eggs</li>
          <li>Kale</li>
            <li>Radishes</li>
            <li>Wholegrain: breads, pasta, rice –- BB vitamins
            </li>
            <li>Fruits: berries, citrus, papaya
            </li>
            </ul>

            <p>NUTRITION FOR THE LUTEAL PHASE</p>
            <br>
            <br>
              <p1>what is happening?
            <br>
            Estrogen and progesterone levels are high. If the egg isn’t fertilized, hormone levels decrease and the menstrual cycle starts again.

            <br> 
            <br>
               FOOD FOCUS:Curb cravings
            <br>
            <br>
               MUST INCLUDE:</p1>
               <ul>
              <li>Cauliflower</li>
              <li>Cucumber (water retention)
            </li>
              <li>Squash</li>
                <li>Caffeine- free herbal teas
               </li>
                <li>Sesame seeds
               </li>
                <li>Spinach</li>
                <li>Brown rice
               </li>
                <li>Protein of choice: tofu, chicken, lean meats, fish and seafood
               </li>
                <li>Berries</li>
                <li>Turmeric latte blend
               </li>
               <li>Dark chocolate
               </li>
                </ul>
        

  

